1
00:00:12,208 --> 00:00:13,875
I'm sorry, Brave Warriors,

2
00:00:13,958 --> 00:00:16,208
but you cannot pass through
the dungeon to Geldabar,

3
00:00:16,291 --> 00:00:17,791
unless you possess the key.

4
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:19,041
So if you want it,

5
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:22,083
I'm afraid you'll have
to do exactly as I say.

6
00:00:22,166 --> 00:00:24,375
This man's a vile sack of flesh.

7
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:25,000
Let's kill him.

8
00:00:25,083 --> 00:00:26,208
We can't.

9
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:28,333
On a journey, a hero
will face many trials.

10
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:30,000
Tell me is this not one of them?

11
00:00:30,083 --> 00:00:32,041
Vile or not,
we have a job to do.

12
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:36,708
[FIGHTER yelling]

13
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:38,791
[MAGE]
Guys, is this really okay?

14
00:00:38,875 --> 00:00:40,166
We're just standing
here watching,

15
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:42,291
while the fighter
does all the work.

16
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,416
She's the one who agreed
to this in the first place.

17
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,666
It's her problem.

18
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:47,083
I didn't become a
hero just to move

19
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:49,416
other people's junk for
them, especially that creep!

20
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,583
[DOG barks]

21
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:52,375
[FIGHTER]
Here, doggy!

22
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:55,375
Chasing after a runaway dog?

23
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:57,500
I guess that's a job for a hero!

24
00:00:57,583 --> 00:00:58,708
[DOG barks]

25
00:00:58,791 --> 00:00:59,750
What the--?

26
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:02,791
Stop it. That tickles.

27
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:04,958
Come on now.
Seriously, I've had enough!

28
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:07,041
Whoa! All right,
that's too much!

29
00:01:07,125 --> 00:01:09,416
No! Stop! Please!

30
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:10,750
You stop that!

31
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,458
No, really, you have to stop!

32
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:14,250
Right now!

33
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:18,500
The mayor invented a potion,

34
00:01:18,583 --> 00:01:20,500
and he wants me to
find out what it does.

35
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:22,833
I guess this is a job
for a hero right?

36
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,791
So... Are you gonna drink it?

37
00:01:24,875 --> 00:01:25,875
For real?

38
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:27,916
Something tells me
that's a bad idea.

39
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,125
Yeah, I'm with her,

40
00:01:29,208 --> 00:01:30,916
a hero should never
have to stoop so low.

41
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,333
So what!

42
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:34,333
In the face of adversity,
a real hero doesn't quit.

43
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:36,375
A real hero fights
till the bitter end!

44
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:37,291
So!

45
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:38,333
[GROUP gasps]

46
00:01:39,958 --> 00:01:43,291
[FIGHTER whimpers]

47
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:46,000
[moans]
My body...

48
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:48,041
It feels all hot and bothered!

49
00:01:48,125 --> 00:01:50,375
It's like I'm burning
up on the inside!

50
00:01:50,458 --> 00:01:51,416
[PALADIN]
What are you doing?

51
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,833
Let go of me right now!

52
00:01:52,916 --> 00:01:54,375
Actually, that feels kinda nice!

53
00:01:54,458 --> 00:01:56,583
On second thought,
don't let go of me right now!

54
00:01:56,666 --> 00:01:57,541
Keep going!

55
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,416
Yes! That's so amazing!

56
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,000
People are starting to stare.

57
00:02:01,083 --> 00:02:02,958
Why don't you two get a room?

58
00:02:03,041 --> 00:02:04,083
Yeah...

59
00:02:04,166 --> 00:02:06,291
Or maybe you'd just
not do it at all!

60
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,458
[FIGHTER screams]

61
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:12,500
[moans] This is an important
mission from the Mayor.

62
00:02:12,583 --> 00:02:14,291
I have got to defeat
this monster!

63
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:16,375
If I do, the key will be mine.

64
00:02:16,458 --> 00:02:18,375
Which means failure
is not an option!

65
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:19,958
I have to keep fighting!

66
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:20,916
[yelps]

67
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,833
[screams]

68
00:02:21,916 --> 00:02:24,625
Stop! I can't take it anymore!

69
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:25,666
[yelps]

70
00:02:27,916 --> 00:02:29,916
Whoa! That sure
was a close call!

71
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,583
Thanks. You saved me.

72
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:32,750
It's like you said,

73
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,166
if we don't find a
way to move forward,

74
00:02:34,250 --> 00:02:35,208
then all could be lost...

75
00:02:35,291 --> 00:02:36,375
You're unbelievable!

76
00:02:36,458 --> 00:02:37,750
Leaving us out in
the cold like that,

77
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:39,750
while you get to have all
of the fun by yourself!

78
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,750
No! You're wrong.

79
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:42,875
This is bad.

80
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:45,166
It doesn't feel good
at all, I promise!

81
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:45,958
--[squelches]
--[moans]

82
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,208
Enough of that!

83
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,708
It's time to finish this!

84
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:49,500
[PALADIN, MAGE]
Alright!

85
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:51,708
Please! Don't! Stop!

86
00:02:51,791 --> 00:02:53,041
Well done!

87
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:55,166
You did everything I asked
of you, Brave Warriors!

88
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,041
You truly are the most
valiant heroes of our time!

89
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,083
Great.

90
00:02:59,166 --> 00:03:00,583
Now hold up your
end of the bargain.

91
00:03:00,666 --> 00:03:02,625
Give our party the key
we need to gain passage

92
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:04,916
through the dungeons to
Geldabar, like you promised!

93
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,583
[MAYOR]
Yes. But don't you see?

94
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,875
The key you seek is
already inside your hearts.

95
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:10,916
[ALL]
Huh?

96
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
By fulfilling my
ridiculous requests,

97
00:03:13,083 --> 00:03:14,625
you and your party
learned the importance

98
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:18,041
of putting the needs and desires
of other people above your own!

99
00:03:18,125 --> 00:03:19,583
Because you've
unlocked this truth,

100
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:22,708
you now have everything you
need to become a real hero.

101
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:24,458
I believed in you from
the very beginning

102
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:27,666
and had all the faith in the
world you wouldn't let me down!

103
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:28,666
So...

104
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,166
I'm gonna hurt him now.

105
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,375
Yeah, sounds good.

106
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:32,250
Go on.

107
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,625
Yeah. Just try not to kill him.

108
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:37,208
[MAYOR screams]

